subproject.description: Social exclusion is more than a re-description of deprivation but a social phenomenon, with its own dynamics and causation, often specific to the country of community in which it occurs. In addition to the growing importance of Europe, Kosovo's many interlinked socio-economic problems and the presence of post-conflict discrimination, ensures that social exclusion is a particularly useful device for understanding deprivation and designing policy responses within the country.

subproject.description: The primary objective of the report is the provision of a high quality piece of research which stimulates public discussion and improves policymaking in the fields of Private Sector and Employment. Yet the overall aims are wider than merely producing a report, and include offering a practical resource to policymakers; and building the capacity of national researchers, through exposure to analysis of an international standard.
